@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Data & Security Notes";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    This classroom project stores sample store data in a local PostgreSQL database.
    The application expects credentials from User Secrets or environment variables, not source-controlled files.
</p>

<ul>
    <li>Use <code>dotnet user-secrets set</code> for development secrets.</li>
    <li>Use <code>ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection</code> in production.</li>
    <li>Keep <code>.env</code> out of Git with <code>.gitignore</code>.</li>
    <li>Use data annotations and Razor validation helpers to reject bad input early.</li>
    <li>Let EF Core parameterize queries instead of building SQL manually.</li>
</ul>
